<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870521-0038 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:McDonnell Douglas Corp.</HL><DD> 05/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MDAEROSPACE (ARO)CONGRESS (CNG) </IN><TEXT>   MCDONNELL DOUGLAS CORP. said congressional authorization committees voted that money be spent to begin an advanced AH-64 Apache helicopter program. The St. Louis-based aerospace concern and defense contractor said the House Armed Services Committee voted to authorize $25 million and the Senate Armed Services Committee recommended $50 million be appropriated to develop the advanced helicopter. McDonnell Douglas said it has targeted 1989 for producing its first operating prototype of the aircraft and plans to deliver the first advanced Apache in 1992. </TEXT></DOC>